steps :

install express, sequelize (ORM) to connect db and perform operations, dotenv to access env variables

- npm install express sequelize dotenv

2 Ways to create models in sequelize

1. by extending Model class provided by sequelize.
   example:

const { Model } = require("sequelize");
const sequelize = require("../config/db");

class Category extends Model {}

Category.init({
id{
constraints...
},
name {
constraints...
}  
},{
other options like,

sequelize,
timestamps: true
})

module.exports = Category

2. by using define method on sequelize database instance
   example:

const sequelize = require("../config/db");

const Cateogory = sequelize.define('Category', {
id: { constraints },
name: { constraints }
},{
timestamps: true  
})

module.exports = Category

create resources using sequelize-cli

- first of install sequelize-cli

  -> npm i sequelize-cli
  -> npm i -g sequelize-cli # globally

# generate assets (folders) like, config/config.json, models, seeders, migrations folders

-> npx sequelize-cli init

#
